OL,3,CMiners strike 40 years on: 12 key
OL,4,Cdates in a dispute that divided Britain
OL,6,FHere is a timeline of some of the key
OL,7,Fevents over that year:
OL,9,F5 March 1984
OL,11,FNational Coal Board (NCB) chairman Ian
OL,12,FMacGregor, hired by Prime Minister
OL,13,FMargaret Thatcher, lit the fuse on the
OL,14,Fstrike with his announcement of 20
OL,15,Fplanned pit closures.
OL,17,FSome local strikes begin at Yorkshire
OL,18,Fcollieries, including Cortonwood near
OL,19,F. The National Union of Mineworkers
OL,20,F(NUM) believed more were earmarked for
OL,21,Fclosure.
