OL,3,CMiners strike 40 years on: 12 key
OL,4,Cdates in a dispute that divided Britain
OL,6,FKnown as the Battle of Orgreave, it
OL,7,Fsaw 93 arrests. More than 50 pickets
OL,8,Fand 72 policemen were injured. Ninety-
OL,9,Ffive pickets were charged with riot,
OL,10,Funlawful assembly and similar
OL,11,Foffences. To this day there are calls
OL,12,Ffor miners to be exonerated.
OL,14,FPrime Minister Margaret Thatcher
OL,15,Frefers to the striking miners as the
OL,16,F"enemy within" in a speech to the
OL,17,Fgovernment's backbench 1922 committee.
OL,19,F19 November
