OL,3,CMiners strike 40 years on: 12 key
OL,4,Cdates in a dispute that divided Britain
OL,6,FNearly a year to the day from the
OL,7,Fstrikes at Cortonwood, the NUM calls
OL,8,Foff the strike following a vote of 98
OL,9,Fto 91 in favour of a return to work.
OL,10,FTwo days after announcing the result
OL,11,Fin London, Scargill joins a march at
OL,12,FBarrow Colliery near Barnsley. He says
OL,13,Fthe campaign against job losses will
OL,14,Fcontinue. Margaret Thatcher speaks of
OL,15,Fher relief that miners will return to
OL,16,Fwork.
